Sik sik iceri giriyorum, herkes nazik. Cesitli musterilerle ilgilendiklerini biliyorum, ancak tekrarlanan kibar musterilere karsi kaba ve tutarsiz olmayin. Ayrica iki adet vape satin aldim. Bunlari koridorda deneyebilecegimi soyledi, sadece ayakta durmak ve hatta bir vape denemek icin biraz garip bir alan yaptim, birisi benim icin kapiyi acik tuttu ve ben de yolculugumla bulusmak zorunda oldugum yerin kapisindan zar zor cikmistim. Bir nefes daha aliyorum ve elektronik sigara cekisinin kapali oldugunu ve tadi biraz bozuk oldugunu fark ettim, sadece bir tanesi digerinde iyiydi. Bunun biraz asiri oldugunu ve elektronik sigaranin cekildigini ve tadi tuhaf oldugunu ve para iadesi bile yerine degistirilmesini takdir ediyorum, elektronik sigaralari iade etmediklerini biliyorum, zaten sebepsiz yere elektronik sigaralari iade etmiyorum. Ona digerinin iyi oldugunu ama bunun tadi tuhaf ve cekici oldugunu soyluyorum, sonra da onun onunde bana mi denetir? Yani simdi sorun yok ama daha once koridorda olmasi gerekiyordu bana sanki bir yalanciymisim gibi bakti ve ne yapmam gerektigini soyledi ve tadin konuyla alakali bir konu olmadigi ya da biraz duman gordugunden beri boyle bir yorum yaptigi hakkinda yorum yapti. featured_reviews.review_id:
I worked at She Bop up until 2 days ago. I loved this place with all my heart when I first started working here 2.5 years ago. I've made amazing memories with the staff and am so grateful for each of you. I loved working with customers, meeting them in such a vulnerable place, and easing their anxieties while helping them figure out what is best for them. It really makes me emotional. Like any business, there are flaws of course. However, the positives had always vastly outweighed the negatives- that is, up until about 10 months ago.

From here on out, when I refer to the "staff" I am referring to everyone but the owner/GM... Since Jeneen Doumitt took sole ownership of this company, I have slowly lost hope for the future of She Bop. It sounds dramatic I know, but without a proper HR department, management (read: the owner) is able to always operate within a grey area of muddled procedures and ever-changing policies that only ever benefit those at the top and allow them to micromanage our days.

Before working at She Bop, I actually worked in Human Resources for 5 years. The problem here is there are no checks-and-balances. No witnesses to conversations had or advocates for staff who fear retaliation when speaking up. That's the danger in being a part of a "family" at work. The current owner has created an environment that rewards those who stay complicit with a smile and punishes those who verbalize any opinion other than her own. She can be condescending, unreasonable, and committed to her opinion and her opinion alone. Even when staff members speak up politely, they are labeled "disrespectful" and regularly overlooked for career advancement opportunities.

The recent comments on the Instagram post were also upsetting to so many. For the last few days, it has shaken our staff and affected us all deeply. Still, management has yet to open a conversation with us about it. When asking the general manager whether they will speak to the staff about it, she said she didn't know. "Why? Do you think we should?" Yes. Yes I do. It is unfair for the staff to be pushed aside and spoken for. I was especially upset when the Instagram post was signed off as "Team Bop," making it sound like we all agreed with everything posted when this is not true.

I personally have been advocating for better benefits and wages for a while now, in check ins, speaking directly with other staff members, and in a one-on-one with Jeneen earlier this year. It is clear to me that she is so far removed from the reality of living off a wage of $17-21/hour that she either does not understand or does not care. She certainly does not understand why more staff members don't take advantage of the IRA contribution match program. "It's basically free money," she said to me while laughing. I explained to her that many staff members do not even make enough to pay for groceries or health insurance- how would they have enough to contribute to an IRA account? But that does not matter to her.

I had a meeting scheduled with Jeneen to discuss a pay raise this weekend. However, over the last few weeks, I have thought long and hard about my future here and have come to the conclusion that with the state of the company right now, I have none. With this in mind, advocating for myself right now is neither here nor there. featured_reviews.review_text:
I worked at She Bop up until 2 days ago. I loved this place with all my heart when I first started working here 2.5 years ago. I've made amazing memories with the staff and am so grateful for each of you. I loved working with customers, meeting them in such a vulnerable place, and easing their anxieties while helping them figure out what is best for them. It really makes me emotional. Like any business, there are flaws of course. However, the positives had always vastly outweighed the negatives- that is, up until about 10 months ago.

From here on out, when I refer to the "staff" I am referring to everyone but the owner/GM... Since Jeneen Doumitt took sole ownership of this company, I have slowly lost hope for the future of She Bop. It sounds dramatic I know, but without a proper HR department, management (read: the owner) is able to always operate within a grey area of muddled procedures and ever-changing policies that only ever benefit those at the top and allow them to micromanage our days.

Before working at She Bop, I actually worked in Human Resources for 5 years. The problem here is there are no checks-and-balances. No witnesses to conversations had or advocates for staff who fear retaliation when speaking up. That's the danger in being a part of a "family" at work. The current owner has created an environment that rewards those who stay complicit with a smile and punishes those who verbalize any opinion other than her own. She can be condescending, unreasonable, and committed to her opinion and her opinion alone. Even when staff members speak up politely, they are labeled "disrespectful" and regularly overlooked for career advancement opportunities.

The recent comments on the Instagram post were also upsetting to so many. For the last few days, it has shaken our staff and affected us all deeply. Still, management has yet to open a conversation with us about it. When asking the general manager whether they will speak to the staff about it, she said she didn't know. "Why? Do you think we should?" Yes. Yes I do. It is unfair for the staff to be pushed aside and spoken for. I was especially upset when the Instagram post was signed off as "Team Bop," making it sound like we all agreed with everything posted when this is not true.

I personally have been advocating for better benefits and wages for a while now, in check ins, speaking directly with other staff members, and in a one-on-one with Jeneen earlier this year. It is clear to me that she is so far removed from the reality of living off a wage of $17-21/hour that she either does not understand or does not care. She certainly does not understand why more staff members don't take advantage of the IRA contribution match program. "It's basically free money," she said to me while laughing. I explained to her that many staff members do not even make enough to pay for groceries or health insurance- how would they have enough to contribute to an IRA account? But that does not matter to her.

I had a meeting scheduled with Jeneen to discuss a pay raise this weekend. However, over the last few weeks, I have thought long and hard about my future here and have come to the conclusion that with the state of the company right now, I have none. With this in mind, advocating for myself right now is neither here nor there. I hope that they instead use this time to discuss how to best open a dialogue with the staff about what has been going on this past week. I hope that Jeneen has the courage to ask the staff what they need to be happy here. I hope they all have the courage to be honest. Support each other. There is strength in numbers and change is possible. We can take pride in this company and the good it does while also encouraging it to be even better.

If anyone would like to know more about my experience here, please reach out to me.
featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
2 gun oncesine kadar She Bop'ta calisiyordum. Bundan 2,5 yil once burada calismaya basladigimda burayi tum kalbimle sevmistim. Personelle harika anilar biriktirdim ve her birinize cok minnettarim. Musterilerle calismayi, onlarla bu kadar hassas bir yerde bulusmayi ve endiselerini hafifletirken kendileri icin en iyisinin ne oldugunu anlamalarina yardimci olmayi seviyordum. Bu beni gercekten duygulandiriyor. Her iste oldugu gibi bu isin de kusurlari var elbette. Ancak, yaklasik 10 ay oncesine kadar, olumlu seyler her zaman olumsuzluklardan cok daha agir basiyordu.

Su andan itibaren, "personel" dedigimde, sirket sahibi/GM disindaki herkesi kastediyorum... Jeneen Doumitt bu sirketin tek mulkiyetini aldigindan beri, She Bop'un gelecegine dair umudumu yavas yavas yitirdim. Kulaga dramatik geliyor biliyorum, ancak uygun bir IK departmani olmadan, yonetim (yani: sahip) her zaman yalnizca en tepedekilere fayda saglayan ve onlara mikro yonetim olanagi taniyan, karmasik prosedurlerin ve surekli degisen politikalarin oldugu gri bir alanda faaliyet gosterebilir. gunlerimiz.

She Bop'ta calismaya baslamadan once aslinda Insan Kaynaklari'nda 5 yil calistim. Buradaki sorun, kontrol ve dengenin olmamasidir. Konusurken misilleme yapilmasindan korkan personelin konusmalarina tanik olmadi veya onlari savunan kimse olmadi. Isyerinde bir "ailenin" parcasi olmanin tehlikesi budur. Simdiki sahibi, suca ortak olanlari gulumseyerek odullendiren, kendi fikri disinda herhangi bir fikri dile getirenleri ise cezalandiran bir ortam yaratmis. Kucumseyici, mantiksiz olabilir ve yalnizca kendi fikrine ve fikrine bagli olabilir. Personel uyeleri kibarca konussalar bile "saygisiz" olarak etiketleniyorlar ve kariyer ilerleme firsatlari duzenli olarak goz ardi ediliyor.

Instagram gonderisine yapilan son yorumlar da pek cok kisiyi uzdu. Son birkac gundur kadromuzu sarsti ve hepimizi derinden etkiledi. Ancak yonetim henuz bizimle bu konuda bir gorusme baslatmadi. Genel mudure bu konuyu personelle konusup konusmayacaklarini sordugunda ise bilmedigini soyledi. "Neden? Yapmamiz gerektigini mi dusunuyorsun?" Evet. Evet ediyorum. Personelin bir kenara itilmesi ve adina konusulmasi haksizliktir. Instagram gonderisinin "Takim Bop" olarak imzalanmasi beni ozellikle uzdu; bu dogru olmadigi halde paylasilan her seyde hemfikirmisiz gibi bir izlenim yaratti.

Ben kisisel olarak bir suredir, check-inlerde, diger personelle dogrudan konusarak ve bu yilin baslarinda Jeneen ile birebir gorusmelerde daha iyi sosyal haklar ve ucretleri savunuyorum. Bana gore saat basina 17-21 dolar maasla gecinme gerceginden o kadar uzak ki ya anlamiyor ya da umursamiyor. Daha fazla personelin neden IRA katki eslestirme programindan yararlanmadigini kesinlikle anlamiyor. Gulerken bana "Temelde bedava para" dedi. Ona, bircok personelin yiyecek veya saglik sigortasi icin odeme yapmaya bile yetmedigini, bir IRA hesabina katkida bulunmaya nasil yetecek kadar para kazanabileceklerini anlattim. Ama bu onun icin onemli degil.

Bu hafta sonu maas artisini gorusmek uzere Jeneen ile bir toplantim vardi. Ancak son birkac haftadir buradaki gelecegim hakkinda uzun uzun dusundum ve sirketin su andaki durumu goz onune alindiginda hicbir gelecegim olmadigi sonucuna vardim. Bunu akilda tutarak, su anda kendimi savunmak ne burada ne de orada. Umarim bu zamani, gecen hafta olup bitenler hakkinda personelle en iyi sekilde nasil diyalog baslatabileceklerini tartismak icin kullanirlar. Umarim Jeneen personele burada mutlu olmak icin neye ihtiyaclari oldugunu sorma cesaretine sahiptir. Umarim hepsinin durust olma cesareti vardir. Birbirinizi destekleyin. Sayilarda guc vardir ve degisim mumkundur. Bu sirketle ve yaptigi iyiliklerle gurur duyabilir, ayni zamanda onu daha da iyi olmasi icin tesvik edebiliriz.

Buradaki deneyimim hakkinda daha fazla bilgi edinmek isteyen biri varsa lutfen bana ulasin.

featured_reviews.review_id: Amazing place! My child is trans FTM(15) and has been having body issues.
